      "description": [
        "Dark screamo duo exploring the tension between identity, fear, and the pressure we place on ourselves in the face of uncertainty. The feeling of \"not arriving on time to your own life,\" oscillating between disappearing and asserting your existence, searching for clarity within the chaos. For fans of Portrayal of Guilt, Ostraca, Saetia, Respire, Infant Island, Lightning Bolt, Hella, and The Body.",
        "Oshira sharpened their live thing playing rooms like House of Vans in Mexico City. \"Vorágine\" was recorded and mixed by the duo themselves, with mastering by Brad Boatright and cover art by Ethan Lee McCarthy."
